  "prompt": "The current year is 2014. Why is this the 21st century and not the 20th century?",
  "response": "The reason the years 2000-2099 are considered part of the 21st century, while years like 1900-1999 were part of the 20th century, is due to how centuries are counted.\n\nCenturies are counted starting from year 1, not year 0. So:\n- The 1st century spans from year 1 to year 100\n- The 2nd century spans from year 101 to year 200\n- The 3rd century spans from year 201 to year 300\n\nAnd so on...\n\nFollowing this pattern:\n- The 20th century spans from year 1901 to year 2000\n- The 21st century spans from year 2001 to year 2100\n\nSo in 2014, you are in the 21st century, even though it might seem counterintuitive at first. This is why the year 2000 marked the beginning of the 21st century, not the end of the 20th century.",
